                        <div class="home__data">
                            <h1 class="home__title">Olasunkanmi Arowolo</h1>
                            <h3 class="home__subtitle">Background</h3>
                            <p class="home__description">
                                Olasunkanmi Arowolo is an dedicated Assistant Lecturer and PhD researcher (University of Kent) specialising in Journalism. With an achievement of earning his Bachelor's degree at the age of 22 from Lagos State University (LASU), Arowolo distinguished himself as the youngest academic staff member upon his employment in 2017. He brings a strong background in media production to his work, providing a unique perspective that blends both academic and industry experience.
                                <br> 
                                <br> 
                                Known for his innovative approach to education, Arowolo has made headlines for pioneering the use of a mobile classroom. By leveraging digital technology, he enhances the learning experience for his students and ensures they are equipped with the skills necessary in today's digital age. This forward-thinking mindset exemplifies his commitment to staying at the forefront of educational advancements.
                                <br> 
                                <br> 
                                Arowolo's research interests revolve around advancing journalism practices and exploring innovative approaches. He has founded the Pan-African Journal Database, a valuable resource aimed at digitising journals of African origin. Through this initiative, Arowolo seeks to improve the global visibility of research originating from Africa, making it more accessible and impactful.
                                <br> 
                                <br> 
                                Recognised for his outstanding commitment to education, Arowolo is a highly regarded lecturer in the Department of Journalism at the esteemed School of Communication. Hailing from Iba in Ojo Local Government Area of Lagos State, he expertly combines his academic expertise with industry experience to inspire and educate the next generation of journalists. With his passion for journalism and dedication to academic excellence, Arowolo is making significant contributions to the field and shaping the future of journalism education.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

